author: Bloomberg
title: The clacking of Chinese plants returns as rest of world goes in Coronavirus quarantine
description: Employees are returning to work, production lines are starting to roll, even in Wuhan.
content:
While much of the world’s output is grinding to a halt because of the coronavirus, China is slowly emerging from its shutdowns by restarting production at factories and resuming some flights.
